29/08/2005
BUCHAREST, Romania -- The economy ministry announced on Saturday (27 August) that the drafting of the new national strategy for the defence industry would be completed by 7 September. The document would focus primarily on restructuring measures for Brasov-based plants administered by the state-run company Romarm.
In other news, Deputy Prime Minister Marko Bela says government officials will meet with Hungarian officials in late October. The focus would be on concrete bilateral projects and issues related to the environment and minorities. (Nine o'clock - 29/08/05; 26/08/05)
